Best practices
To reduce the potential risks of using a SAS, Microsoft provides some guidance:

To securely distribute a SAS and help prevent man-in-the-middle attacks, always use HTTPS. The most secure SAS is user delegation. Use it wherever possible because it removes the need to store your storage account key in code. Microsoft Entra ID must be used to manage credentials; this option might not be possible for your solution. Try to set your expiration time to the smallest useful value.

